**What Changed**
- Added [jit_load.h](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/runtime_io/jit_load.h) / [jit_load.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/runtime_io/jit_load.cpp) with:
  `torch::jit::Module load_jit_serialized(const std::string& path);`
- Implementation is a thin pass-through with a function-local `static std::mutex`.
- Swept 34 call sites across:
  `aoti_encoder_main.cpp`, `decode_main.cpp`, `density_main.cpp`, `finalize_main.cpp`, `lib/scheduler/steady_batch_primitive.h`, `lib/session/runtime.cpp`, `lib/session/session.cpp`, `pipeline_main.cpp`, `steady_main.cpp`, `ws_server.cpp`.
- Added [check_no_raw_jit_load.sh](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/scripts/check_no_raw_jit_load.sh).
  It prefers `rg` and falls back to `grep` because the build container lacks `rg`.
- Wired `jit_load_guard` into CMake and made `nemotron_runtime` depend on it. Added `jit_load.cpp` to `nemotron_runtime`; standalone swept harnesses also link `nemotron_runtime`.

